    <title> CheckPoint: Pendulum Period Comparisons </title>
    
      <br/>
      <p>A rubber band can be cut into pieces of different lengths. A block of mass m, suspended on a single piece of such rubber band that has a length d, would have oscillations of period T. Now consider the following systems, built of different pieces of that rubber band and different blocks. The systems are marked A, B, C and D, as shown in the diagram.</p>
      <p>Remember: "T" in this problem is the period of oscillations, not the tension.</p>
    
